  abstract = {CMake is an extensible, open-source system that manages the build
	process in an operating system and compiler independent manner. Unlike
	many cross-platform systems, CMake is designed to be used in conjunction
	with the native build environment. CMake can compile source code,
	create libraries, generate wrappers, and build executables in arbitrary
	combinations. CMake supports in-source and out-of-source builds,
	and can therefore support multiple builds from a single source tree.
